status_message: Tips: Deer are most active from 6-9 p.m. Hi-beams when possible. 1 deer = more nearby. Swerving can cause more danger. http://tr.im/zZHE
New Jersey & Nebraska have seen the largest recent deer collision increases: 3 today for every 2 in 2004. http://tr.im/zZHE
Deer collisions are most common during the deer migration/mating season: October through December. http://tr.im/zZHE
Image: Map of the likelihood of a deer collision in your state: http://tr.im/A0v6
Top 5 states in which auto/deer collisions are most likely: 1-W.Va. 2-Mich. 3-Penn. 4-Iowa 5-Mont. http://tr.im/zZHE
Avg. property damage from an auto/deer collision: $3,050. These collisions cause over 150 human fatalities per year. http://tr.im/zZHE
A vehicle in W. Va. has a 1 in 39 chance of striking a deer in the next year, versus a 1 in 9,931 chance in Hawaii. http://tr.im/zZHE
Vehicles on U.S. roads have risen by 7% in 5 years, but for whatever reason, deer collisions are up 18%. http://tr.im/zZHE
West Virginia, for the 3rd year in a row, remains the U.S. state where auto/deer collisions are most likely. http://tr.im/zZHE
Auto/deer collisions occur 100,000 times a month in the U.S. That's 1 every 26 seconds! http://tr.im/zZHE
Today we released our latest deer-vehicle collision stats. See them all: http://tr.im/zZHE. I'll also share tidbits throughout the day.

This storm is, at the time and for many years to come, the most devastating natural disaster in U.S. history. State Farm Fire and Casualty Company, the parent company's property insurer, pays a record $4 billion to its customers to help them recover and rebuild after Hurricane Andrew. Who is one person in your life that is always there when you need them the most?

IBM designed the ECHO computer system especially for State Farm agents in 1980. This was one of American business' first widespread uses of computing for consumer transactions. What was your first computer?

In 1964, State Farm sold its one-millionth homeowners insurance policy to a couple in Ohio. Also that year, State Farm became the #1 U.S. insurer of homes, and continues to this day to protect more homes than any other insurer in the country.

State Farm History Lesson: 1955
The IBM 650, the Company's First Computer ‚Äì In 1955, CEO Adlai Rust inspects the IBM 650. This was, at the time, a major technological advance ‚Äì a computer that could store 10,000 characters in its memory. Today's smartphones have 800,000 times the memory of the IBM 650. What single piece of technology has made the greatest impact in your life?

Home Office Building, 1930 ‚Äì Known today as the "downtown building," it served as the home office for State Farm from 1929 to 1972. What's an interesting bit of trivia about the building you live or work in?

When State Farm started, most of its agents were part time farmers selling insurance on the side. One hundred and seventy five agents gathered in Bloomington for the company's first convention in 1925. What's your family's greatest moment ever captured in a photo?
